post_title: Vintage Michael L. Kungl Club de Metro Framed Art Print
post_content:
American artist Michael L. Kungl's wields a spatter airbrush and oil paint to create flamboyant, vintage images in his trademark “21st Century Art Deco” style. Producing posters with bold colors, streamlined shapes, elegant lettering and cinematic angles, Kungl works at high magnifications for meticulous detailing. Before pursuing fine art full time, he created logos, designs and package illustrations for major corporations for more than 20 years. Two years later, he was selected to create the official artwork for Miami Beach’s 25th Annual Art Deco Weekend. Kungl’s work is featured in magazines, how-to books, television shows, gift items and home décor products.

post_content:
Franz Marc was a German expressionism artist whose work captured animals in unusual and eye catching colors. This wonderful piece is called 'Two Cats, Blue and Yellow 1912' and it shows two cats curled up together as they enjoy an afternoon nap. The glaring simplicity of his work was bursting with an emotional presence that was visible through his use of mainly primary colors and thick, predominant brush strokes.
